Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
saveModel(25.10)                                              saveModel(25.10)

Name
       saveModel  -  Saves block level design information for top level imple-
       mentation

Syntax
       saveModel

        [-help]

        -dir <string>

        [-ilm]

        [-sdf]

        [-spef]

        [-stream [-mapFile string][-outputMacros]]

       Saves block level design information for top level implementation.  You
       can  use this command after block implementation. The saveModel command
       saves the following data by default:

              * LEF

              * DEF

              *

                Innovus DB (*.enc.dat)

       For timing library  (.lib)  generation  you  need  to  use  the  do_ex-
       tract_model command.

Parameters
       -dir <string>
              Specifies  the name of the directory where you want to write the
              files. You can specify an additional level of hierarchy  to  de-
              fine the model design stage, for example:

              results_conv_model/postRoute/...

              results_conv_model/signoff/...

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each saveModel parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man saveModel.

       -ilm   Generates ILM models.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -mapFile <string>
              Specifies the file used for layer mapping. This file is required
              for successful stream out, and is read by the next tool used  in
              the design flow.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -outputMacros
              Writes  LEF  abstract information such as LEF pin geometries and
              obstructions for macros. Writes one text label per port within a
              LEF macro pin plus one text  label  per  shape  for  feedthrough
              pins. For more information, see streamOut.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -sdf   Generates the delay data for each view in MMMC mode or for setup
              and hold modes.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -spef  Generates  parasitic data if a design is at least routed. It in-
              vokes extraction, if not already extracted. For  extraction,  it
              honors the default, detailed or CCE mode user settings.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -stream
              Generates Stream data, if the design is routed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
              * The   following  command  creates  a directory called cts_con-
                dor_dma that contains the LEF (.lef and antenna.lef) files un-
                der the library directory, delay  and  parasitic  information,
                and the design data of dma block:

                saveModel -sdf -spef -dir cts_condor_dma

